cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with emergent communication between agents in referential games. It also involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. 

The paper also involves computer vision techniques and the use of realistic images, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on learning and capturing visual semantics suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. 

The use of self-supervised learning and the exploration of different tasks in the game suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of neural networks and the exploration of different weights for the feature extractor suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
